]
},
"children":[
{
"type":"p",
"hlId":"bffc74",
"children":[
"The four ",
{
"type":"no-wrap",
"children":[
{
"type":"abbreviation",
"title":"pulmonary function test",
"children":[
"PFT"
]
},
"s"
]
},
" commonly used to measure static lung function are spirometry, flow-volume loops, lung volumes, and ",
{
"type":"no-wrap",
"children":[
{
"type":"abbreviation",
"title":"diffusing capacity of lung for carbon monoxide",
"children":[
"D",
{
"type":"tag",
"tagName":"small",
"attrs":{
},
"children":[
"LCO"
]
}
]
},
"."
]
}
]
}
]
},
{
"type":"section",
"id":"mk19_bb_pm_s1_2",
"title":{
"__html":"Key Tests and Patterns"
},
"titleNode":{
"type":"section-title",
"hlId":"afee13",
"children":[
"Key Tests and Patterns"
]
},
"children":[
{
"type":"p",
"hlId":"156cf0",
"children":[
{
"type":"tag",
"tagName":"b",
"attrs":{
},
"children":[
"Spirometry"
]
},
" is used to diagnose airflow obstruction such as asthma, ",
{
"type":"no-wrap",
"children":[
{
"type":"abbreviation",
"title":"chronic obstructive pulmonary disease",
"children":[
"COPD"
]
},
","
]
},
" and bronchiectasis."
]
},
{
"type":"list",
"children":[
" ",
{
"type":"list-item",
"hlId":"23476d",
"children":[
{
"type":"abbreviation",
"title":"forced expiratory volume exhaled in 1 second",
"children":[
"FEV",
{
"type":"tag",
"tagName":"sub",
"attrs":{
},
"children":[
"1"
]
}
]
},
"/",
{
"type":"abbreviation",
"title":"forced vital capacity",
"children":[
"FVC"
]
},
" <0.7 (or below the ",
{
"type":"abbreviation",
"title":"lower limit of normal",
"children":[
"LLN"
]
},
") indicates airflow obstruction."
]
},
" ",
{
"type":"list-item",
"hlId":"f0526f",
"children":[
"A ≥12% increase in either FEV",
{
"type":"tag",
"tagName":"sub",
"attrs":{
},
"children":[
"1"
]
},
" or FVC and an increase ≥200 mL from baseline in either parameter with bronchodilator therapy indicates reversible airway obstruction."
]
},
" ",
{
"type":"list-item",
"hlId":"b8d1ab",
"children":[
"Equal reductions in FEV",
{
"type":"tag",
"tagName":"sub",
"attrs":{
},
"children":[
"1"
]
},
" and FVC suggest restrictive lung disease."
]
},
" "
]
},
{
"type":"p",
"hlId":"d814de",
"children":[
{
"type":"tag",
"tagName":"b",
"attrs":{
},
"children":[
"Lung volume"
]
},
" measures include total lung capacity (TLC), vital capacity (VC), functional residual capacity (FRC), expiratory reserve volume (ERV), and residual volume. The ",
{
"type":"abbreviation",
"title":"total lung capacity",
"children":[
"TLC"
]
},
" is normal or even increased in pure obstructive disease and decreased in restrictive diseases."
]
},
{
"type":"p",
"hlId":"55062b",
"children":[
{
"type":"tag",
"tagName":"b",
"attrs":{
},
"children":[
"D",
{
"type":"tag",
"tagName":"small",
"attrs":{
},
"children":[
"LCO"
]
}
]
},
" evaluates gas transport across the alveolar-capillary membrane."
]
},
{
"type":"inline-wrap",
"wrapId":"1",
"contentIds":[
"mk19_bb_pm_s1_inline_t1"
],
"forceOpen":true
},
{
"type":"p",
"hlId":"574afa",
"children":[
{
"type":"tag",
"tagName":"b",
"attrs":{
},
"children":[
"Flow-volume loops"
]
},
" can help localize anatomic sites of airway obstruction. Refer to the “Flow-Volume Loops” figures."
]
},
{
"type":"inline-wrap",
"wrapId":"3",
"contentIds":[
"mk19_bb_pm_f01"
],
"forceOpen":true
},
{
"type":"heading",
"class":"tricked",
"children":[
"Don't Be Tricked"
]
},
{
"type":"list",
"class":"tricked",
"children":[
" ",
{
"type":"list-item",
"hlId":"fa50c8",
"children":[
"In patients with low lung volumes, a normal D",
{
"type":"tag",
"tagName":"small",
"attrs":{
},
"children":[
"LCO"
]
},
" suggests an extrapulmonary cause (e.g., obesity)."
]
},
" "
]
},
{
"type":"inline-wrap",
"wrapId":"2",
"contentIds":[
"mk19_bb_pm_s1_inline_t2"
],
"forceOpen":true
},
{
"type":"heading",
"class":"tricked",
"children":[
"Don't Be Tricked"
]
},
{
"type":"list",
"class":"tricked",
"children":[
" ",
{
"type":"list-item",
"hlId":"a70f8d",
"children":[
"Pulse oximetry is normal in patients with carbon monoxide and cyanide poisoning."
]
},
" ",
{
"type":"list-item",
"hlId":"c58123",
"children":[
"Pulse oximetry may be falsely low in patients with shock."
]
},
" "
]
}
]
}
]
},
